name: Blue Eyes That Ring True: My Cat Panquecito
description:
This is a photo of my cat Panquecito.
 (Panquecito means Little Pound Cake)

I wrote this poem inspired by Panquecito:

BLUE EYES THAT RING TRUE

LIKE CLOUDS WALKING GRACEFULLY

LIKE SKIES FILLED WITH PROMISE

BLUE EYES THAT LOOK AT YOU

THEY STAND FOR HOPE AND PEACE FOR THE LAND

THEY SHINE LIKE THE BLUE LAGOON IN ICELAND

BLUE EYES AS BEAUTIFUL AS BLUEBELL WOODS

THEY GIVE SO MUCH GRACE

WITH ONE LOOK YOU FEEL BLESSED

BLUE EYES THAT MAKE YOU AS HAPPY AS A NEVER ENDING SUNNY DAY

BLUE TWINKLE

BLUE STARS

BLUE FOUNTAIN OF BLISS

BLUE RAIN THAT MAKES CROPS GROW

BLUE BUBBLE GUM THAT TASTES SWEET

BLUE HOUR

BLUE HOUSE OF INSPIRATION

TAKE A LOOK INTO THE BLUE

AND YOU MIGHT SEE A PART OF YOU

REFLECTED BACK LIKE SHINING MIRRORS

TAKE A LOOK INTO THE BLUE

BLUE EYES THAT RING TRUE
